N2  - I hope that the various comments in this month's column will excite the reader's imagination, stimulating him to contribute either to this column or to the Journal. Although the term ?information systems? is often equated with computers, there is no need to do this. There were information systems long before there were computers, and information often flows today without the aid of computers, nearly as often in spite of them.
